Resolution Steps
Phase 1 – Firmware Preparation
	• Downloaded official BIOS from manufacturer support
	• Verified motherboard compatibility and BIOS integrity
	• Validated file authenticity
Phase 2 – USB Flash Preparation
	• Prepared dedicated USB drive (FAT32)
	• Stored BIOS file exclusively on USB
Phase 3 – Safe Baseline Establishment
	• Entered UEFI BIOS
	• Reset BIOS to factory defaults
	• Cleared overclock and voltage customizations
	• Disabled custom memory profiles
Phase 4 – Firmware Flash Execution
	• Accessed BIOS update utility
	• Selected BIOS file from USB
	• Initiated flash process with uninterrupted power
	• Monitored completion; system auto-rebooted
Phase 5 – Post-Flash Configuration Restoration
	• Reconfigured BIOS manually
	• Restored custom CPU, SSD, port, and memory settings
Phase 6 – Boot & Stability Validation
	• Saved BIOS configuration
	• Successful POST and Windows boot
	• Multiple reboots validated stability
